KDevelop 0.4

KDevelop will be an easy to use IDE (Intergrated Development Enviroment) for
Unix/X11.At the moment there are only alpha-versions.

KDevelop-Homepage:
http://www.cs.uni-potsdam.de/~smeier/kdevelop/

Requirements:
In order to successfully compile und use KDevelop, you need following
programs and libraries: 	

	g++ 2.8/egcs 1.1 (or compatible) (it should work with gcc 2.7.2)
	GNU make
	perl 5.004
	autoconf 2.12
	automake 1.2
	Qt 1.42
	KDE 1.1
 	KDE-SDK  (optional)
	sgmltools  (optional)
	Glimpse 4.1 (optional)
	KIconEdit (optional)
	KDbg  (optional)
	a2ps  (optional)
	enscript  (optional)
	Gv,Ghostview,KGhotsview  (optional)


Installation:
see INSTALL in the same directory

Have fun!
							 The KDevelop-Team

FAQ:

How can I convert a KDevelop 0.2 project to a 0.3 one?

1. please change the AC_OUTPUT in the configure.in to a oneline version

for example: 
old version AC_OUTPUT(Makefile \
		kdevelop/kwrite/Makefile \
		kdevelop/templates/Makefile
)
new version: AC_OUTPUT(Makefile kdevelop/kwrite/Makefile kdevelop/templates/Makefile)

2. That's all. :-)


